title: For Sale:  Early Colt .45 Lightweight Commander, Mfg. 1953, Another Collectible Colt From Jackson Armory!
postcontent:
Early Colt Lightweight Commander .45, Mg. 1953.In the 1950’s most Police Officers and Detectives still carried revolvers as duty guns, but, as always, the guys on the “cutting edge” were already starting to switch over to automatics, and the 4$ barreled, Lightweight Colt Commander was (and still is!) an excellent choice for both holster and concealed carry – a lightweight, high-quality handgun with .45 acp firepower! This early 1953 gun has a factory blue finish with polished flats and matte slide top and undercarriage. It has fixed sights and the desirable ring hammer. The magazine is Colt-marked on the bottom. The factory grips are brown plastic with the Rampant Colt emblem. These early Commanders, obviously, pre-dated the Series 70 and Series 80 guns. The pistol has some tiny service marks and faint holster wear, the grips are in great shape, and overall condition is close to 95%. The pistol has a shiny bore with strong rifling, and trigger pull is exceptionally smooth. This is a very collectible Colt Lightweight Commander, it will really enhance a good collection! Rare Springfield Armory M1A Super Match .308/7.62 sitting in a McMillan stock from the factory.

The Springfield Super Match M1A is a semi-automatic rifle chambered in 7.62 NATO or .308 Win. The M1A is a civilian version of the famous M14, which was once a standard issue US military rifle and known to be very accurate and reliable. Springfield offers eight different models of the M1A.

The Super Match is very similar to the National Match, but the difference is the Super has a Douglas air gauged heavy match barrel. Air gauged quality means designers pushed air through the barrel and measured the amount that escaped. The process determines the tolerance (or consistency of design) of the bore. It basically proves the barrel shoots accurately and keeps a tight seal on the propellant gases as they push the projectile out the bore. It also has a rear lugged receiver that increases

The Super Match is gas-operated, so propellant gases are captured by a tube near the muzzle, which directs the gas into a valve on the bolt, and the gas pushes the bolt back so it can eject a spent casing and chamber a fresh round.

Its features include a national match two-stage trigger that sets off the action with a 4.5- to 5-pound pull. A match hooded rear sight aperture that’s like looking through a pinhole. It’s also adjustable for windage and elevation. It has a fixed blade front sight. 


Springfield recommends the Super Match for precision and competitive shooting.

title: For Sale:  Noreen -- Bad s 338 Lapua ULR AR-10
postcontent:
The Noreen Bad News .338 Lapua ULR (Ultra long Range) Rifle This rifle is modeled after the AR platform however the take down pins are farther apart than the AR-10 and AR-15 rifles causing the rifle to not accept an interchangeable upper like the AR-15 and AR-10 platform.

This rifle does use some AR parts like the pistol grip, stock and trigger allowing for them to be changed. The magazine on this rifle comes in a 5 or 10 round proprietary magazine.

The innovative Noreen Bad News .338 Lapua ULR provides tactical marksmen with the performance of a powerful and proven long range cartridge with the numerous advantages of the venerable AR platform. Weighing just 13 pounds, the Bad News .338 Lapua ULR is light enough and portable enough to serve as a patrol rifle, yet it vastly outperforms comparable bolt-action sniper rifles.

The rifle’s custom muzzle brake and semi-automatic action significantly suppress recoil. With no bolt to manually work, the smooth action semi-automatic action allows the shooter to keep his head in the scope and his eye on the target for rapid, accurate follow-up shots. In the AR tradition, the Bad News .338 Lapua ULR disassembles quickly for easy cleaning, then reassembles with no loss of zero. The familiar fit and feel of a conventional AR rifle makes the transition to the more powerful sniper rifle virtually seamless.
